Neighbors of the McMartin Pre-School reacted today to the conclusion of the molestation  trial against former teachers Raymond Buckey and his mother, Peggy McMartin Buckey,  who were acquitted of 52 charges on Thursday.
Residents of the upper-middle-class  suburb agreed the case poisoned everyone associated with it.
Sue Brown was convinced  they were guilty.
Alan Lagunoff, whose son testified, was disappointed in both sides.
He  would like the deserted, rundown, school to become a center for abused children.
Brenda  Platt would like it torn down and considered the case a disgrace.
Linda Geisert was  disappointed in the legal system and the jurors. 
